zensim_strip_vs_full_2026-05-26.csv
====================================
Measured by: crates/zensim-gpu/examples/strip_measure_actual.rs
Date: 2026-05-26
Host: water-cooled AMD Ryzen 9 7950X + RTX 5070, CUDA 13.2.1
Workspace: zenmetrics--zensim-strip-port (master HEAD after Phase 5 commit)
Command pattern:
    cargo build --release -p zensim-gpu --example strip_measure_actual --features cuda
    target/release/examples/strip_measure_actual <full|strip> <basic|ext|iw> <w> <h>

`peak_delta_mb` = nvidia-smi `memory.used` after compute - baseline (process start).
This INCLUDES cubecl runtime pool overhead (~193 MB).

Key findings:
- 4096² WithIw: Full 2722 MB → Strip 482 MB (5.6× reduction)
- 8192² WithIw: Full 10205 MB → Strip 705 MB (14.5× reduction)
- Strip WithIw at 8192² (705 MB) is ~1.4× of Strip Basic (513 MB)
  — confirms the regime asymmetry from issue #16 is closed: WithIw
  strip mode uses memory comparable to Basic strip mode, mirroring
  CPU zensim's flat-across-regimes structural cost.

Strip default h_body = 256, halo = 40.
